      "wikitext": "{{Infobox\n|eng         = Scarecrow\n|source      = [[Crafting]]\n|season      = [[Spring]] • [[Summer]] • [[Fall]]\n|recipe      = [[File:Farming Skill Icon.png|24px|link=]] [[Farming]] Level 1\n|ingredients = {{Name|Wood|50}}{{Name|Coal|1}}{{Name|Fiber|20}}\n|sellprice   = Cannot be sold\n}}\nA '''Scarecrow''' is a craftable item that prevents [[Animals#Crows|crows]] from eating [[crops]]. Scarecrows can be crafted at [[Farming]] level 1. Scarecrows are not needed to protect crops grown from [[Crafting#Seeds|Wild Seeds]], since crows do not attack them.\n\nSince there are no crows on [[Ginger Island]], no scarecrows need to be planted on the farm there.\n\n==Range==\nA Scarecrow will protect the surrounding circular area of 249 spaces (including the space its standing on); 8 spaces each to the north, east, south, and west, as well as 6 spaces each to the northeast, southeast, southwest, and northwest. In other words, it protects a 17x17 area, excluding 10 spaces in each corner.\n\n[[File:Scarecrow Range.png|500px]]\n\n==Rarecrows==\n'''Rarecrows''' work the same way as regular Scarecrows, except for the Alien Scarecrow, which hats can be placed on. Soon after collecting all 8 rarecrows (usually the next day) a letter will arrive with the recipe to craft a [[Deluxe Scarecrow]].\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n! Number\n! Image\n! How to Obtain\n|-\n| style=\"text-align: center;\"| 1\n| [[File:Rarecrow 1.png|32px|center]]\n| Purchase at the [[Stardew Valley Fair]] for {{Price|800|Token}}.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align: center;\"|2\n| [[File:Rarecrow 2.png|32px|center]]\n| Purchase at the [[Spirit's Eve]] festival for {{Price|5000}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align: center;\"|3\n| [[File:Rarecrow 3.png|32px|center]]\n| Purchase at the [[Casino]] for {{Price|10000|Qi}}.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align: center;\"|4\n| [[File:Rarecrow 4.png|32px|center]]\n| Purchase at the [[Traveling Cart]] randomly during fall or winter for {{Price|4000}},\nor purchase at the [[Festival of Ice]] for {{Price|5000}}.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align: center;\"|5\n| [[File:Rarecrow 5.png|32px|center]]\n| Purchase at the [[Flower Dance]]  for {{Price|2500}}.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align: center;\"|6\n| [[File:Rarecrow 6.png|32px|center]]\n| Purchase from the [[Dwarf]] for {{Price|2500}}.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align: center;\"|7\n| [[File:Rarecrow 7.png|32px|center]]\n| Donate 20 [[Artifacts]] (not counting [[Minerals]]) to the [[Museum]].<br />''Can be purchased from the [[Night Market]] once the first one is earned.''\n|-\n| style=\"text-align: center;\"|8\n| [[File:Rarecrow 8.png|32px|center]]\n| Donate 40 items to the [[Museum]].<br />''Can be purchased from the [[Night Market]] once the first one is earned.''\n|}\n\n==Quests==\n*Reach [[Farming]] Level 1 and craft a Scarecrow to complete the [[Quests#Advancement|\"Advancement\" Quest]].\n\n==Trivia==\n* Rarecrow #1 is a reference to the Turnip Head character in Hayao Miyazaki's ''Howl's Moving Castle''.\n* Interacting with a Scarecrow shows a message indicating how many crows it has scared away. The counter resets when the Scarecrow is picked up.\n\n==Secrets==\n* [[Secrets#Hats|Hats can be placed on Rarecrow #3 (Alien)]].\n\n==History==\n{{History|1.4.1|Can now purchase museum rarecrows from the Night Market.}}\n\n{{NavboxEquipment}}\n\n[[Category:Craftable items]]\n\n[[de:Vogelscheuche]]\n[[es:Espantapájaros]]\n[[fr:Épouvantail]]\n[[it:Spaventapasseri]]\n[[ja:カカシ]]\n[[ko:허수아비]]\n[[hu:Madárijesztő]]\n[[pt:Espantalho]]\n[[ru:Пугало]]\n[[tr:Korkuluk]]\n[[zh:稻草人]]"
    }
